Plot: Emma Woodhouse is one of Austen's most captivating and vivid characters. Beautiful, spoilt, vain and irrepressibly witty, Emma organizes the lives of the inhabitants of her sleepy little village and plays matchmaker with devastating effect.
Characters: Jane Fairfax, Mr. Woodhouse, Augusta Elton, Mrs Anne Weston, Miss Bates, Isabella Woodhouse, John Knightley, Mr. Elton, Mrs. Elton, Cher, Tai, Josh, Elton, Christian, Mel Horowitz, Lady Toby Geist, Master Wendell Hall
